'''Heroes''' are obtainable units in ''[[AFK Journey]]''. They come in different rarities, belong to a [[Faction]], categorized into a [[Class]], and can wield [[Exclusive Equipment]].

==How to Obtain==
Heroes are primarily obtained via [[Recruitment]] using {{Item|Invite Letter|20|text=Invite Letters}}, {{Item|Epic Invite Letter|text=Epic Invite Letters}}, {{Item|Rate Up Invite Letter|text=Rate Up Invite Letters}}, or {{Item|Stellar Crystal|20|text=Stellar Crystals}}. These [[Recruitment Items]] can be:

* Earned from [[Event]]s and [[Quest]]s.
* Purchased in the [[Emporium]] with various items.
* Purchased with real money in the [[Trolley]] or [[Limited Bundles]].

Other ways to obtain characters include:

* 1st Purchase Reward
** {{Hero|Rowan|nobr=1}} can be obtained as part of the first purchase rewards.
* Quests
** {{Hero|Chippy|nobr=1}} and {{Hero|Hammie|nobr=1}} are obtained at the start.
* Guarantee
** {{Hero|Cecia|nobr=1}} is a guaranteed character on the 10th recruit. One of {{Hero|Smokey & Meerky|nobr=1}}, {{Hero|Hewynn|nobr=1}}, or {{Hero|Rowan|nobr=1}} is chosen at random to be a guaranteed character on the 30th recruit.
* Selector Chests
** Rare chests offer a selection of heroes where one can be chosen and obtained.
* {{Item|Soulstone (A-Level)|25|text=A-Level Soulstones}} and {{Item|Soulstone (S-Level)|25|text=S-Level Soulstones}}.
** Obtain a random {{A-Level}} or {{S-Level}} hero, respectively.
* [[Event]]s
* [[Arena Store]]
** A selection of {{S-Level}} heroes can be purchased with {{Item|Arena Coin|20|text=Arena Coins}} with a monthly limit on each.
* [[Dream Store]]
** A selection of {{A-Level}} heroes can be purchased with {{Item|Dream Fragment|20|text=Dream Fragments}} with a monthly limit on each.
* [[Guild Store]]
** {{Celestial}} and {{Hypogean}} heroes can be purchased with {{Item|Guild Medal|25|text=Guild Medals}} with a monthly limit on each.
* [[Season Store]]
** Heroes from previous [[Season]]s, excluding {{Celestial}} and {{Hypogean}} heroes, can be purchased with {{Item|Season Token|30|text=Season Tokens}} with a monthly limit on each.

==Progression==
===Leveling===
{{See Also|Resonating Hall}}
Heroes are initially leveled individually. Completing the tutorial unlocks Resonance Levels where 5 heroes are selected as the Hands of Resonance and all other heroes match their lowest level. Only the Hands of Resonance can be leveled and Hands of Resonance must be within 10 levels of each other. 

Heroes gain levels using {{Item|Gold}}, {{Item|Training Manual|text=Training Manuals}}, and {{Item|Hero Essence|25}} from Level 1 to Level 240. After unlocking [[Season Story]], heroes can be leveled beyond Level 240 using {{Item|Gold}}, {{Item|Season Manual|25|text=Season Manuals}}, {{Item|Season Essence|30}}, and {{Item|Season Starlight|20}}.

